   {:e #blake3 "bd6400ddd2248fb3af598e40147317ab7fd3b088833c3fa5dd4c53cddfecfeb4" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: CAL-RETEST scored 4.2/10 — concept collapse persists because Otsu calibrates at harvest but observations use bootstrap default before first harvest. Online calibration updates threshold after EVERY observation, converging in 3-5 observations.\n\nAPPROACH: In observe.rs, after computing concept assignments and BEFORE writing CCE datoms, add online calibration:\n\n1. Read current calibration stats from store config:\n   count = get_config('calibration.similarity-count') -> i64, default 0\n   sum = get_config('calibration.similarity-sum') -> f64, default 0.0\n   sum_sq = get_config('calibration.similarity-sum-sq') -> f64, default 0.0\n\n2. If primary concept assignment exists (ConceptAssignment::Joined), add its similarity:\n   count += 1\n   sum += similarity as f64\n   sum_sq += (similarity * similarity) as f64\n\n3. If count >= 3, compute threshold and temperature:\n   mean = sum / count\n   variance = sum_sq / count - mean * mean\n   stddev = variance.max(0.0).sqrt()\n   threshold = (mean - 0.5 * stddev).clamp(0.15, 0.85)\n   temperature = (stddev / 2.0).max(0.01)\n\n4. Write 5 config datoms in the CCE transaction (same tx as concept assignments):\n   :config/calibration.similarity-count -> count.to_string()\n   :config/calibration.similarity-sum -> sum.to_string()\n   :config/calibration.similarity-sum-sq -> sum_sq.to_string()\n   :config/concept.join-threshold -> threshold.to_string()  (only if count >= 3)\n   :config/concept.sigmoid-temperature -> temperature.to_string()  (only if count >= 3)\n\n5. The NEXT braid observe reads the updated threshold at line 615:\n   let join_threshold = get_config('concept.join-threshold').unwrap_or(embedder.join_threshold())\n   This already works — no change needed on the read side.\n\nALGEBRAIC PROPERTIES:\n- Sufficient statistics (count, sum, sum_sq) are a COMMUTATIVE MONOID under addition. CRDT-safe for multi-agent merge.\n- The threshold formula (mean - 0.5*stddev) approximates the lower cluster boundary for roughly Gaussian similarity distributions. The 0.5 coefficient provides moderate selectivity.\n- Clamping to [0.15, 0.85] prevents degenerate thresholds.\n- The existing Otsu at harvest becomes a full-recalculation audit that corrects any drift.\n\nCOST: 5 extra datoms per observation (vs 9+ already written). Negligible.\n\nCONVERGENCE: By observation 3, threshold is computed. By observation 5, the running statistics are stable enough for the threshold to be near-optimal. No chicken-and-egg.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) After 3 observations on fresh store, :config/concept.join-threshold exists. (B) After 5 observations, threshold differs from bootstrap default. (C) By observation 6+, NOT all observations match all concepts. (D) All existing 2034 tests pass. (E) Sufficient statistics datoms are written correctly.\n\nFILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs (~30 lines added after concept assignment block)" :op :assert}
